<br>
Once you have a force gathered, and preparing, the race is over. That's how the race idea works: first with force, has claim. Welcome to the Rathe. The *only* race mobs that work on the &quot;first to pull&quot; principle are those mobs that are out in wide open zones, Talendor, Gorenaire, Kal'orak Dar, etc. Mobs that require preparation and some measure of skill all work the same: first with force has claim. Venril, Trak, Velk, any mob of Vindi's level that you can think of that isn't an outdoor fight, falls clearly under that distinction. <br>
<br>
Just like a force in the cubby doesn't get walked over on the way to trak by another guild, there should be a level of common courtesy maintained for all raid level mobs. Considering Vindi, if anything, is a sight harder in terms of logistics and coordination, the conventions should be more strictly adhered to. I'd like to see SoY do anything with another guild rushing them along all the time, especially one who has had kill experience with the mob in question. <br>
<br>
I'm not surprised, though, some people's kids have never learned to share, the only unfortunate thing is that they've found each other in large enough numbers as to be inconvienent on the Rathe. <br>
<br>
Here's hoping that Bogfather's feelings about Kenshiiro are well deserved, to run over another guild like that takes a level of integrity far below what I've read about Kenshiiro in the past from someone whose opinons I value. <br>
<br>
So what's the deal here? You gank the mob or what? Try to not bring the &quot;kthx plz faggot&quot; people to the board, either. That only makes it look worse. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
